OL,3,CHow will Ofgem's #28bn investment
OL,4,Cimpact your energy bills?
OL,6,FThroughout 2025, Ofgem said it has
OL,7,F"rigorously reviewed spending
OL,8,Fproposals from electricity
OL,9,Ftransmission owners, National Gas, and
OL,10,Fthe gas distribution companies, to
OL,11,Fensure the best value for billpayers".
OL,13,F"We've set strict delivery targets,
OL,14,Fpushed companies to maximise
OL,15,Fefficiency, and rejected bids that do
OL,16,Fnot serve consumers' interests," it
OL,17,Fsaid, claiming this has delivered a
OL,18,Fpotential of #4.5 billion (15%) in
OL,19,Fsavings against initial proposals
OL,20,Fworth #33 billion.
