OL,3,CHow will Ofgem's #28bn investment
OL,4,Cimpact your energy bills?
OL,6,FWhile the price cap did fall a number
OL,7,Fof times since then, these falls were
OL,8,Fsmaller than the increases in 2021 and
OL,9,F2022.
OL,11,FThe October 2025 price cap of #1,755
OL,12,Fis 2% higher than the previous level
OL,13,Fof #1,720 per year paid by a typical
OL,14,Fdual-fuel household paying by Direct
OL,15,FDebit.
OL,17,FWhile this is down from early 2023,
OL,18,F"it remains more than a third (37%)
OL,19,Fabove the levels before the energy
OL,20,Fcrisis", according to energy industry
OL,21,Ftrade association Energy UK.
